Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees (top and middle positions for 4 servings). Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on one half of a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, half the @Italian Seasoning{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4, spread potatoes out across entire sheet.)

Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{10%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

Peel and slice @red onion{1}(peeled and sliced into ½-inch-thick rounds). Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and sliced into strips). Trim and slice @zucchini{1}(trimmed and sliced crosswise into ¼-inch-thick rounds).

In a #medium bowl{}, toss onion and bell pepper with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

Once potatoes have roasted 10 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully toss onion and bell pepper on empty side. (For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting; add veggies to a second baking sheet and roast on middle rack.)

Return to top rack until potatoes are browned and veggies are tender, ~{10-15%minutes} more.

Toss zucchini in same bowl with a drizzle of @cooking oil{3%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini in a single layer; cook until golden brown and slightly tender, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, remaining Italian Seasoning, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} (large drizzle for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Spread half the @sourdough bread{4} slices with a thin layer of aioli. Spread remaining sourdough slices with @roasted red pepper spread{4%oz}.

Fill with even layers of @mozzarella cheese{½%cup}, roasted veggies, and zucchini (we used 4-6 zucchini slices; you may have some left over). Close sandwiches.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for zucchini over medium heat. Once hot, add sandwiches; press down with #spatula{} or #heavy-bottomed pan{}. Cook, pressing occasionally, until bread is toasted and cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes} per side. (For 4 servings, work in batches or use a second pan, adding more oil as necessary.)

> Lower heat if sandwiches begin to brown too quickly!

Halve panini on a diagonal and divide between plates. Serve with potato wedges and remaining aioli on the side for dipping.

> Serve any remaining zucchini slices on the side!